			 Format Query Results as JSON with FOR JSON (SQL Server) 

					 
								 07/18/2017 
							 5 minutes to read 
							 
								 Contributors 
								 
											 
								 

					 In this article 
						 THIS TOPIC APPLIES TO:   SQL Server Azure SQL Database Azure SQL Data Warehouse  Parallel Data Warehouse  Format query results as JSON, or export data from SQL Server as JSON, by adding the  FOR JSON  clause to a  SELECT  statement. Use the  FOR JSON  clause to simplify client applications by delegating the formatting of JSON output from the app to  SQL Server. 
  When you use the  FOR JSON  clause, you can specify the structure of the JSON output explicitly, or let the structure of the SELECT statement determine the output.   
